  <p>
    Early morning swimming has officially begun at ISJ. Last week, the Lions were in the pool bright and early, starting their day with energy, discipline, and no small amount of fun. The new programme marks an exciting addition to the school's sports offering.
  </p>

  <h2>Every Tuesday and Thursday at 6:00 am</h2>

  <p>
    Sessions run every Tuesday and Thursday morning, starting at 6:00 am. It is a commitment that requires real dedication from students and families alike, and the enthusiasm shown in the first week has been wonderful to see.
  </p>

  <p>
    The programme is supported by expert coaches from Pari Sakti Swimming Club, who are working alongside the students to develop their technique, build fitness, and foster a love of the sport. ISJ is grateful for their expertise and energy in getting the programme off to such a strong start.
  </p>

  <h2>Building More Than Swimming Skills</h2>

  <p>
    Early morning sport builds more than physical fitness. The routine and commitment required to be in the pool at 6:00 am helps students develop discipline, resilience, and a positive mindset that carries into the rest of the school day. ISJ is proud to give students the opportunity to start their mornings in the best possible way.
  </p>

</ArticleLayout>
